# Practice â€” Build a Local Server

### Initialize Project

```bash
mkdir local-server
cd local-server
npm init -y
npm install express
```

### Create `server.js`

```js
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.send("Server is running");
});

app.listen(3000, "0.0.0.0", () => {
  console.log("Listening on port 3000");
});
```

Run:

```bash
node server.js
```

Test:

* [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)
* http://<LAN-IP>:3000
